	This person needs to be an HTML/CSS/Javascript expert with at least 2-3 years of relevant experience. They should also be interested in programming back-end.</p>
<p>
	The person we are currently after will, in their own right need to be with the following characteristics:</p>
<ul>
	<li>
		* Able to create user interfaces from scratch</li>
	<li>
		* Able to not only implement, but also innovate and suggest improvements (both process and code)</li>
	<li>
		* Can lead/nurture freshers into independent developers</li>
	<li>
		* Can work in an Agile/Scrum environment, with tight yet realistic deadlines</li>
	<li>
		* Has a fair knowledge of the whole LAMP stack, especially Javascript and PHP</li>
</ul>
<p>
	We are not good at spoon feeding - so we are after problem solvers. If you were here last few weeks in this position, you would have:</p>
<ul>
	<li>
		* Written, rewritten and minified Javascript code for our JS heavy front-end</li>
	<li>
		* Worked on WebGL based framework for a new aspect of our tutorial using impress.js</li>
	<li>
		* Worked on challenging CSS fixes as well as implemented whole new designs for our product langoor.net</li>
	<li>
		* Written backend code and created database tables to support your front-end efforts on langoor.net</li>
	<li>
		* Helped setup a Hudson server on CentOS and Ubuntu, enabling us to do continuous integration/deployment</li>
	<li>
		* Setup back-end integrations on some features from a front-end perspective</li>
</ul>
<p>
	We want people who:</p>
<ul>
	<li>
		* Are currently in Bangalore</li>
	<li>
		* Can start within 30 days notice period</li>
	<li>
		* Want to work in a startup environment (and have an entrepreneurial instinct); want to be a big cog in a small machine, not a small cog in a big machine</li>
	<li>
		* Want to work in the Unix/Linux environment</li>
</ul>
<p>
	We recommend they review langoor.net before they apply.</p>
